description: CodeNovia website brand and build constraints
globs:
  - "src/**/*"
alwaysApply: true
---

# CodeNovia

- Stack: Next.js App Router + TypeScript + Tailwind v4 + Framer Motion. No custom backend; contact uses Formspree later.
- Brand: deep navy `#050B18`, accent cyan/blue `#1E9BFF` / `#3DB4FF`, fonts Outfit (display) + DM Sans (body). Dark premium tech look.
- Primary CTA label: "Let's Talk Business" → `/contact`.
- Logo: temporary SVG in `components/brand/Logo.tsx` — swap later in one place.
- Content: prefer `src/lib/data/*` over hardcoding copy in many files.
- Do not redesign the Home visual language; match existing sections when adding pages.
- Out of scope for v1: CMS, auth, Three.js, light mode, i18n, blog posts.
- **Git/GitHub:** Never run git or GitHub commands (`git init`, commit, push, gh, etc.). The user handles all git/GitHub themselves. Do not create or modify `.gitignore` unless they explicitly ask.
